151
00:07:46,560 --> 00:07:48,440
They are more or less our distant relatives.

152
00:07:49,200 --> 00:07:50,120
But if the whole family

153
00:07:50,280 --> 00:07:51,840
all uses the surname Zhou,

154
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:53,160
it might be confusing.

155
00:07:53,400 --> 00:07:54,840
So we're used to calling people

156
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:56,120
just by the characters in their given name.

157
00:07:57,840 --> 00:07:58,480
Indeed.

158
00:07:58,720 --> 00:08:00,160
There are a lot of people, so it helps us distinguish.

159
00:08:08,640 --> 00:08:10,360
Why are you carrying a bag

160
00:08:10,480 --> 00:08:11,560
in the car?

161
00:08:22,720 --> 00:08:23,520
Give it to me.

162
00:09:19,920 --> 00:09:20,680
Come on up.

163
00:09:25,720 --> 00:09:27,480
Do you want to come to my house?

164
00:09:32,080 --> 00:09:34,200
Is it too late?

165
00:09:35,120 --> 00:09:36,920
I'd like to make you some medicinal tea to keep the cold away.

166
00:09:37,680 --> 00:09:38,560
It takes about 20 minutes.

167
00:09:38,720 --> 00:09:39,760
Half an hour at most.

168
00:09:42,360 --> 00:09:44,200
But I've never

169
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:45,200
entered

170
00:09:45,360 --> 00:09:46,400
a girl's house.

171
00:09:49,680 --> 00:09:50,840
Didn't you say

172
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:52,800
you like Wu Ge's embroidery?

173
00:09:53,360 --> 00:09:54,880
How come you're so…

174
00:09:57,240 --> 00:09:59,160
So unromantic?

175
00:10:01,080 --> 00:10:01,600
A little.

176
00:10:10,720 --> 00:10:11,960
I want to ask you a question.

177
00:10:13,760 --> 00:10:14,320
Go ahead.

178
00:10:15,200 --> 00:10:17,040
You said that the two of us

179
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:18,960
are one of your research areas.

180
00:10:19,280 --> 00:10:21,040
What if this research is in the wrong area?

181
00:10:23,200 --> 00:10:23,840
You're making a

182
00:10:23,880 --> 00:10:25,120
conceptual error.

183
00:10:25,800 --> 00:10:27,360
What conceptual error?

184
00:10:28,840 --> 00:10:29,840
The research area itself

185
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:31,600
can't be right and wrong.

186
00:10:31,720 --> 00:10:33,440
Only the method of experimentation can be wrong.

187
00:10:35,880 --> 00:10:37,800
And what if the experimental method is wrong?

188
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:40,120
If the experimental method is wrong,

189
00:10:40,240 --> 00:10:41,400
we can change the method.

190
00:10:41,800 --> 00:10:42,640
But the research area itself

191
00:10:42,800 --> 00:10:44,080
will not change.

192
00:10:47,840 --> 00:10:49,400
That sounds very convincing.

193
00:10:52,440 --> 00:10:53,720
For example, the fact that

194
00:10:54,760 --> 00:10:55,840
we're together

195
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:57,160
is not going to change.

196
00:10:58,040 --> 00:11:00,000
If something goes wrong,

197
00:11:00,680 --> 00:11:01,560
we can

198
00:11:01,760 --> 00:11:03,360
change the way we get along.

199
00:11:06,680 --> 00:11:07,360
Science and technology

200
00:11:07,520 --> 00:11:08,960
are not only the greatest productive force.

201
00:11:09,160 --> 00:11:10,680
They're also the best language.

202
00:11:11,880 --> 00:11:12,240
Let's go.

203
00:11:22,200 --> 00:11:22,840
Come on in.

204
00:11:24,360 --> 00:11:25,880
This is the house I bought myself.

205
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:26,680
Xiaoyu and I share it.

206
00:11:26,840 --> 00:11:27,760
She lives in that room.

207
00:11:31,640 --> 00:11:33,200
Sit down first. I'll make some medicine for you.

208
00:12:02,400 --> 00:12:03,360
What are you doing?

209
00:12:05,440 --> 00:12:06,280
Nothing.

210
00:12:06,360 --> 00:12:08,160
I just think it's cute.

211
00:12:08,640 --> 00:12:09,320
It's Xiaoyu's.

212
00:12:12,400 --> 00:12:13,560
You should wrap up in spring and wear less in autumn.

213
00:12:13,720 --> 00:12:14,800
Don't be in such a hurry to wear

214
00:12:14,960 --> 00:12:16,280
your summer clothes in spring.

215
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:17,880
The weather has been changing a lot in the past ten days.

216
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:18,920
It's easy to catch a cold.

217
00:12:20,320 --> 00:12:21,840
I just have a mild cold.

218
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:23,000
I don't need to drink medicine.

219
00:12:23,440 --> 00:12:24,760
This is herbal medicine to dispel the cold.

220
00:12:24,920 --> 00:12:25,720
If it's a cold,

221
00:12:25,880 --> 00:12:27,080
you'll feel better within a day.

222
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:29,760
It works so well?

223
00:12:30,120 --> 00:12:31,040
Of course it does.

224
00:12:33,320 --> 00:12:34,480
You didn't think

225
00:12:34,640 --> 00:12:35,680
I deliberately made an excuse

226
00:12:35,840 --> 00:12:36,920
to get you to come up, did you?

227
00:12:41,040 --> 00:12:42,560
In fact, just now downstairs,

228
00:12:42,800 --> 00:12:44,520
I didn't mean to say no.

229
00:12:45,360 --> 00:12:46,480
I just thought

230
00:12:46,800 --> 00:12:47,760
I did the engagement thing

231
00:12:47,880 --> 00:12:49,120
out of blue.

232
00:12:49,520 --> 00:12:51,600
So I want to take things slowly.

233
00:12:53,720 --> 00:12:56,360
But really I did want to come up.

234
00:12:58,280 --> 00:12:59,520
He feels shy now.

235
00:13:00,440 --> 00:13:01,560
You sounded calm

236
00:13:01,720 --> 00:13:02,800
when you proposed.

237
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:04,440
Yet now you're shy.

238
00:13:07,680 --> 00:13:08,920
Next time you want to come up,

239
00:13:09,160 --> 00:13:10,000
just say so.

240
00:13:16,520 --> 00:13:17,480
You're in a hurry to leave?

241
00:13:20,520 --> 00:13:21,880
I have to go back to Zhenjiang

242
00:13:22,040 --> 00:13:23,200
tonight.

243
00:13:23,440 --> 00:13:25,280
I'll have dinner with my family tomorrow morning.

244
00:13:26,480 --> 00:13:27,760
You're driving back overnight?

245
00:13:27,880 --> 00:13:29,240
Then finish this and go.

246
00:13:31,640 --> 00:13:33,000
I don't mean to kick you out.

247
00:13:33,200 --> 00:13:34,920
I just mean if you leave now,

248
00:13:35,040 --> 00:13:36,560
you can at least get two hours of sleep at home.

249
00:13:36,720 --> 00:13:38,240
Otherwise you won't get any sleep at all.

250
00:13:41,200 --> 00:13:41,880
Okay.

251
00:13:43,480 --> 00:13:43,720
No need to...

252
00:13:48,520 --> 00:13:49,960
You didn't waste a drop, that's good.

253
00:13:51,080 --> 00:13:52,080
Let's go. I'll see you off.

254
00:14:07,920 --> 00:14:09,440
I came back early this time

255
00:14:09,800 --> 00:14:10,880
because you were

256
00:14:11,040 --> 00:14:12,120
nominated for the award.

257
00:14:12,880 --> 00:14:14,160
You found out so quickly!

258
00:14:14,360 --> 00:14:15,680
My agent just told me.

259
00:14:16,720 --> 00:14:17,280
Congratulations.

260
00:14:18,200 --> 00:14:19,280
I may not win.

261
00:14:20,400 --> 00:14:21,360
So

262
00:14:21,520 --> 00:14:23,000
you're back for the award presentation?

263
00:14:24,320 --> 00:14:25,320
Kind of.

264
00:14:25,880 --> 00:14:27,640
The rest of my time will be spent

265
00:14:27,800 --> 00:14:29,240
preparing for the engagement ceremony.

266
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:34,280
I'll head back, then.

267
00:14:34,520 --> 00:14:36,400
I'll come back on the day of the award presentation.

268
00:14:36,880 --> 00:14:37,360
Okay.

269
00:14:47,760 --> 00:14:48,280
Bye.

270
00:15:06,880 --> 00:15:09,240
That room on the 12th floor is the bathroom.

271
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:11,360
It looks like the heating lamp is on.

272
00:15:12,280 --> 00:15:13,240
She's probably in the shower.

273
00:15:14,160 --> 00:15:15,080
I'm back.

274
00:15:15,840 --> 00:15:16,960
I went out for something to eat.

275
00:15:21,160 --> 00:15:22,040
Smells like Chinese medicine.

276
00:15:22,440 --> 00:15:23,360
You had some Chinese medicine?

277
00:15:24,400 --> 00:15:25,160
Haven't you always hated

278
00:15:25,160 --> 00:15:26,080
this smell?

279
00:15:27,440 --> 00:15:28,760
I didn't want to disappoint her.

280
00:15:29,160 --> 00:15:30,520
It's just a cup of Chinese medicine.

281
00:15:32,120 --> 00:15:35,400
It's just a cup of Chinese medicine.

282
00:15:37,560 --> 00:15:38,240
Chen.

283
00:15:39,080 --> 00:15:41,520
Actually I really wanted to ask

284
00:15:41,680 --> 00:15:44,480
the two of you…

285
00:15:44,640 --> 00:15:45,920
You want to ask me

